\subsubsection{winding number}
\label{TI/Lecture notes/1:winding-number}
\(H(k)=\mathbf{h}(k)\cdot \mathbf{\sigma}\), \(\mathbf{h}(k)=0\) is a
degenerate point with \(|v|=|w|\), two bands cross, define
\(h(k)=h_x(k)+ih_y(k)\), we have
